Project 5 - Intro to Animation Programming

Project to display GPU-based morph target animation.
Includes skeletal animation and display, exploring forward kinematics and target animation using a vertex shader

Instructions:
Run VS and build the program. Launch the program and Animal3D will open.
Select FILE, hover over Load Demo... , and select Animal3D Demo Plugin to launch the program.
To operate the controls:
Press '<' and '>'  to flip through demo modes, this will load on Demo Mode 4 which is for this project.
Press 'j' and 'k' to change the Render Mode
Press 'J' and 'K' to change the Render Pass between Composite and Scene
Use left click and drag to rotate, use wasd to move around the scene. Zoom in with the mouse wheel.
Press 'P' to reload the shaders
